# Investment Banking

| Term | Definition | Example |
|------|------------|----------|
| Investment Bank | Financial institution providing trading, advisory, underwriting and capital market services. | HSBC, JPMorgan |
| Financial Market | Marketplace where financial products are traded. | FX Market |
| Client | Customer trading with the bank. | ABC Motors |
| Counterparty | Other party involved in a trade. | ABC Motors |
| Dealer | Person executing trades. | FX Trader |
| Trader | Person responsible for buying/selling financial instruments. | FX Dealer |
| Asset | Resource having financial value. | Cash |
| Liability | Financial obligation owed by the bank. | Customer Deposit |

