# Risk Management Glossary

| Term | Definition | Example |
|------|------------|----------|
| Risk | Possibility of financial loss. | FX Movement |
| Market Risk | Loss due to market price movement. | USD rises |
| Credit Risk | Counterparty fails to pay. | ABC Motors defaults |
| Liquidity Risk | Insufficient funds to settle obligations. | No USD available |
| Operational Risk | Failure of systems, process or people. | Batch Failure |
| Risk Appetite | Maximum acceptable risk. | USD 50M |
| Risk Tolerance | Acceptable variation around appetite. | ±2M |
| Exposure | Current outstanding financial risk. | USD 58M |
| Temporary Exposure | Short-term excess with mitigation plan. | Hedge pending |
| Permanent Exposure | Long-term excess without mitigation. | Exposure > Limit for days |
| Hedge | Offset trade reducing exposure. | Sell USD 8M |

